## Actions
/tmp/build_stack.py now hand-assigns only class methods to stages; every
module-level segment (function, dataclass, const) is assigned by a fixpoint
over the reference graph: stage(segment) = min stage among referencing
segments. A post-build assertion verifies every module-level name is
referenced within the stage that introduces it. Stage 1 shrank 472 -> 221
lines: imports, storage records (referenced by _init_storage annotations),
class + lifecycle, parity stubs. Also rebased the stack base onto the new
master (fd7eced353) since local master advanced during review.

## Errors & Mistakes
First rebuild of the top branch restored AGENTS.md from the old-base
monolith, silently reverting master's new "Generated Files" section — caught
by diffing against master and fixed by re-applying only the fake-backend
additions onto master's AGENTS.md. Lesson: after a base move, never restore
shared files wholesale from a backup built on the old base.

